    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - CAB - TILT: 9600 AND 9700 SLEEPER AND NON-SLEEPER CABS -
        CAB DOOR COMPONENTS DISASSEMBLY AND REASSEMBLY - DOOR GLASS
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc id="hl1600615" svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="3">
        <title>DOOR GLASS</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Remove</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove access panel as covered under
                    <hotlnk document="s16006_28.xml" xrefid="hl1600614">DOOR HARDWARE TRIM AND ACCESS PANEL
                        <xref refid="hl1600614"/>
                    </hotlnk>
                    .
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Lower window glass to bottom of its channel.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove two glass fastener screws from window and remove guide from window regulator
                    lever (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1600633">Figure 33</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1600633" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1600633" filename="../figg16/G1600633.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                    <caption>Figure 33. Window Regulator Guide</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. WINDOW REGULATOR GUIDE</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. WINDOW GUIDE RETAINING SCREWS</callout1>
                        <callout1>3. WINDOW CHANNEL RETAINING SCREW</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove mounting bolt and loosen window front run channel (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1600633">Figure 33</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Raise regulator lever for clearance.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Pull glass out bottom of access opening (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1600634">Figure 34</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1600634" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1600634" filename="../figg16/G1600634.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                    <caption>Figure 34. Removing or Installing Window Glass</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Install</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Insert window glass through access opening and into front and rear run channels (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1600634">Figure 34</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Secure front run channel with mounting screw (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1600633">Figure 33</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Lower window regulator lever to bottom of glass.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Engage window guide with regulator lever and secure window guide to glass with two
                    fastener screws (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1600633">Figure 33</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Operate window regulator lever to assure free movement of window through its complete
                    travel. Be sure window glass is secure in run channel. If excessive looseness is encountered, the
                    following steps must be taken:
                </para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Lower window.</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Pull back glass run channel (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f1600635">Figure 35</hotlnk>).
                    </para>
                    <figure id="f1600635" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="g1600635" filename="../figg16/G1600635.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                        <caption>Figure 35. Door Glass Adjustment</caption>
                        <calloutgroup>
                            <callout1>1. FOAM TAPE</callout1>
                            <callout1>2. GLASS RUN CHANNEL</callout1>
                        </calloutgroup>
                    </figure>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Install strip of tape to the upper portion of the glass run frame. A 1/2 inch (12.7
                        mm) wide PVC foam tape approximately 1/8 inch (3.2 mm) thick and 4 inches (102 mm) long is
                        recommended.
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Push glass run channel back into place and check for looseness.</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">If still loose, add additional material to either front or rear glass run frame as
                        required.
                    </para>
                    <specpara>
                        <note>
                            <para>Glass run frame adjustment at lower end of frame can also help resolve looseness.
                            </para>
                        </note>
                    </specpara>
                </step2>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
